%I A397308 #14 Jul 21 2026 00:33:32
%S A397308 7,9,11,13,23,25,31,37,43,47,57,67,71,73,79,85,95,101,103,107,109,113,
%T A397308 121,123,125,151,155,157,161,173,177,187,197,203,205,211,249,257,263,
%U A397308 277,283,289,299,313,317,323,329,341,347,349,365,367,371,377,379,393,397,401,409,425
%N A397308 Positive numbers m such that m - 2^k is a prime for exactly two values of k > 0.
%C A397308 Equivalently, numbers m that have exactly 2 representations of the form m = p+2^k, with k > 0 and p prime.
%C A397308 Only odd terms are present in this sequence, since even numbers have 0 or 1 such representation (A397305 for 0, A397306 for 1).
%F A397308 A397307(a(n)) = 2.
%e A397308 7 is a term because 7-2=5, 7-4=3, then 3 and 5 are primes; also, as 7-2^k is prime for all k > 0, 7 is in A039669.
%e A397308 23 is a term since 23-2=21, 23-4=19, 23-8=15, 23-16=7, and only 7 and 19 are primes.
%Y A397308 Cf. A397305, A397306, A397307.
%K A397308 nonn,new
%O A397308 1,1
%A A397308 _Bernard Schott_, Jul 16 2026
